  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you factory reset an iPhone 4 without a computer?",
  "response": "To factory reset an iPhone 4 without using a computer, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Back Up Your Data**: If possible, make sure to back up any important data as a factory reset will erase everything on your device.\n\n2. **Open Settings**: Go to the home screen and tap on the \"Settings\" app to open it.\n\n3. **Navigate to General**: In the Settings menu, scroll down and tap on \"General\".\n\n4. **Find Reset Options**: Scroll to the bottom of the General settings and tap on \"Reset\".\n\n5. **Select Erase All Content and Settings**: In the Reset menu, tap on \"Erase All Content and Settings\".\n\n6. **Enter Your Passcode**: If prompted, enter your device passcode to confirm.\n\n7. **Confirm Factory Reset**: You will be asked to confirm your choice. Tap \"Erase iPhone\" or \"Erase\" to start the process.\n\n8. **Wait for the Device to Reset**: The iPhone will take some time to erase all data and reset to factory settings. Once complete, the device will restart, presenting you with the initial setup screen as it was when it was new.\n\nAfter following these steps, your iPhone 4 will be reset to its factory default state and ready for new setup.",
